s and sunlit slopes. It drives toward the viewer with a low, angular front end, black grille area, dark headlight surrounds, and amber running lights. The hood has a raised vent or scoop detail, emphasizing the car’s performance look. As it comes closer, the red nose fills the view, then the car sweeps past, revealing its side profile: a compact, aerodynamic coupe with dark-tinted glass, black side mirrors, and silver wheels. The road and hillside slide by in warm daylight.\n\nBack inside a car, the same dark-haired male driver is seen from the front, framed by the steering wheel at the bottom. He wears a dark jacket over a light shirt, and his seat belt crosses his chest. He smiles broadly while driving, hands near the wheel, with sunlit greenery visible through the windshield and side windows.\n\nThe silver station wagon is then shown in motion on an open road at dusk or late afternoon. It passes from a side view into a rear view, its boxy wagon shape and large rear window clear against a pale sky. The taillights and amber lights glow as it travels away along the lane, with trees and low landscape on either side.\n\nThe red sports coupe returns on the hillside road, now seen from a wider angle as it travels along the curve. It leans visually with the road’s angle, its red body catching the warm light while the green hillside rises behind it. The car continues smoothly along the pavement, reinforcing the contrast between the practical wagon and the sporty coupe.\n\nThe commercial ends on a black background with a bold red “NISSAN” wordmark across the center. White, streak-like lettering sweeps across the foreground, partially obscuring the logo and creating a sense of motion.",
